258
00:30:07,500 --> 00:30:08,700
Make it super-size.

259
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:13,200
She said we could get some fruit.

260
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:45,800
- You have to earn the food.
- How do you earn it?

261
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:49,400
Put in your time. Take one of those.

262
00:31:03,300 --> 00:31:07,400
I was so high, I didn't notice
my visa had run out.

263
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:10,400
I couldn't pay the fine to leave.

264
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:15,300
A bloke I met said he'd pay the fine
and give me some pocket money.

265
00:31:15,700 --> 00:31:19,800
I just had to take some packets
and stuff them inside me.

266
00:31:20,100 --> 00:31:23,000
You're telling that
smack-in-the-box tale again?

267
00:31:23,200 --> 00:31:25,800
Yankee girl.

268
00:31:28,900 --> 00:31:32,300
- What's with her?
- She thinks you're fun to piss off.

269
00:31:32,700 --> 00:31:37,000
You're the new show
at the brokedown palace.

270
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:41,200
- When's checkout time?
- Check out anytime, man.

271
00:31:41,500 --> 00:31:45,300
You find freedom here
and in here...

272
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,400
...and in here.

273
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:40,000
- What's with her?
- She thought she'd get pardoned.

274
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:44,100
Everybody thinks they'll get a pardon
from the crown. Makes me sick.

275
00:32:44,500 --> 00:32:48,700
Addicted to fantasy. That road
leads straight into the ground.

276
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:58,400
It happened at least once.
The old mama-san...

277
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:01,500
...she was here one day
and gone the next.

278
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:05,300
- The guards were in a proper lather too.
- What happened?

279
00:33:05,700 --> 00:33:07,200
Nobody knows.

280
00:33:07,500 --> 00:33:12,200
We think a certain guard opened
the gate, and she just walks away.

281
00:33:13,500 --> 00:33:15,400
Which guard was it?

282
00:33:15,700 --> 00:33:18,600
Velie. We think Velie.

283
00:33:22,300 --> 00:33:24,800
So someone bribed Velie? With what?

284
00:33:25,100 --> 00:33:28,500
I heard it was $ 100 for the gate
and a car waiting.

285
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:31,500
Please. If they catch you escaping...

286
00:33:31,900 --> 00:33:34,400
...they add 15 years to your sentence.

287
00:33:34,700 --> 00:33:37,700
Mama-san could have been shot
in the street.

288
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:40,600
All this talk is a waste of time.

289
00:33:40,700 --> 00:33:43,900
You should get in touch
with Yankee Hank.

290
00:33:44,300 --> 00:33:46,600
- Who?
- Yankee Hank.

291
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:52,100
- He's a barrister. That's a stretch.
- Yankee Hank's a damn good lawyer.

292
00:33:54,300 --> 00:33:57,400
If he's so good,
how come you never called him?

293
00:33:57,700 --> 00:34:00,600
An impoverished soul like myself?

294
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:03,400
He like American folding money.

295
00:34:03,700 --> 00:34:05,000
You're not lying.

296
00:34:05,300 --> 00:34:09,600
Of course, if I had the dosh,
I'd try Velie first.

297
00:34:44,500 --> 00:34:45,800
Dad!

298
00:34:47,700 --> 00:34:48,900
I'm so sorry.

299
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:50,400
What?

300
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:53,100
I'm sorry I lied about Hawaii.

301
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:55,100
Honey, it's all right.

302
00:34:55,400 --> 00:35:00,100
We're gonna get you out of here.
Don't worry. Whatever it takes.

303
00:35:00,500 --> 00:35:02,300
Tell everyone I didn't do it.

304
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:07,200
- What?
- We didn't do it!

305
00:35:07,500 --> 00:35:10,600
They know that. Everybody
knows that, baby.

306
00:35:10,900 --> 00:35:13,700
Everybody back home
misses you, sweetie.

307
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:18,700
- Why would you want to come here?
- I'm so sorry.

308
00:35:19,100 --> 00:35:22,000
That's all right.
We'll find a way, okay?

309
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:25,400
Everything is gonna work out,
I promise.

310
00:35:25,700 --> 00:35:27,300
It'll be okay.

311
00:35:28,900 --> 00:35:31,000
I love you.

312
00:35:43,100 --> 00:35:45,400
He's going to get us out.

313
00:35:45,700 --> 00:35:49,200
- He said us?
- Yeah, he wants to see you.

314
00:35:58,200 --> 00:36:01,200
You always thought
you were so smart.

315
00:36:02,700 --> 00:36:05,000
I hope you're proud of yourself.

316
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:08,600
- Mr. Davis...
- You're a schemer.

317
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:12,200
You think I don't know you?
You are dead wrong.

318
00:36:12,700 --> 00:36:15,900
Every word out of your mouth is a lie.

319
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:20,600
Six years old, paint on your hands,
on our couch.

320
00:36:21,100 --> 00:36:22,700
"I didn't do it."

321
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:27,700
16 years old, the beer cans
in my car. "I didn't do it."

322
00:36:28,300 --> 00:36:31,000
Let me hear you say it again.

323
00:36:31,300 --> 00:36:33,400
Say it in here.

324
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:36,100
Come on, for old times' sake.

325
00:36:38,300 --> 00:36:41,100
I didn't do it!

326
00:36:47,300 --> 00:36:49,300
I'm so glad he's here.

327
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:52,100
He's being so great about it.

328
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:55,400
He really knows
how to grease the wheels.

329
00:36:55,700 --> 00:36:58,000
He'll know what to do.

330
00:36:58,300 --> 00:37:00,400
- What's the matter?
- Nothing.

331
00:37:00,700 --> 00:37:03,000
- Why aren't you excited?
- I am.

332
00:37:03,500 --> 00:37:06,100
Did he tell you
he spoke to your dad?

333
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:08,200
Goddamn it!

334
00:37:08,500 --> 00:37:09,400
You like?

335
00:37:09,700 --> 00:37:11,000
Good fish heads.

336
00:37:12,700 --> 00:37:15,500
No! It's a matter of days now.

337
00:37:47,300 --> 00:37:50,100

I told the detective the truth.

338
00:37:50,700 --> 00:37:55,900
I told him about Nick Parks and all
the events leading up to our arrest.

339
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:00,600
I signed a statement...

340
00:38:00,900 --> 00:38:04,600
...assuming it was just a translation
of what I said.

341
00:38:05,100 --> 00:38:09,500
But these aren't my words.
I never said any of that.

342
00:38:09,900 --> 00:38:12,500
That's the truth.

343
00:38:39,300 --> 00:38:42,300
- What happened?
- Don't worry, we'll appeal.

344
00:38:42,600 --> 00:38:46,600
You can request a pardon.
He found you both guilty.

345
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:49,700
- For how long?
- Good news. It wasn't life.

346
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,300
You both got numbered sentences.

347
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:55,800
- For how long?
- 33 years.

348
00:38:56,200 --> 00:38:59,900
- Daddy!
- Honey, I'll take care of everything.

349
00:39:04,600 --> 00:39:06,800
Yes, we're all over it.

350
00:39:07,100 --> 00:39:09,100
Listen, I gotta go.

351
00:39:10,100 --> 00:39:12,700
Sorry about that. Couldn't be helped.

352
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:16,400
- I know how you must feel.
- Fellas, look...

353
00:39:16,800 --> 00:39:19,600
I know what goes on around here.

354
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:22,100
They take drugs seriously.

355
00:39:22,500 --> 00:39:24,800
- There's no doubt...
- Come on.

356
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:29,600
Nobody here really wants
to stop the drugs. They're all...

357
00:39:32,600 --> 00:39:37,600
I don't care if Thailand drowns
in heroin. That's their business.

358
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:41,600
Your business is to help
American citizens.

359
00:39:42,900 --> 00:39:45,300
She didn't do anything.

360
00:39:45,600 --> 00:39:49,400
They're not gonna make
an example of my little girl...

361
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:51,800
...with some trumped-up charge.

362
00:39:52,100 --> 00:39:54,400
You pull strings all the time.

363
00:39:54,700 --> 00:39:58,400
You could pull them for my daughter.

364
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:03,700
The DEA will continue
our investigation.

365
00:40:04,100 --> 00:40:08,900
If we find the alleged man
who lured your daughter into this...

366
00:40:09,300 --> 00:40:12,500
...we'll certainly
introduce that in an appeal.

367
00:40:14,900 --> 00:40:17,600
I know this is difficult for you.

368
00:40:17,900 --> 00:40:21,500
But the best thing
you can do is go home.

369
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:25,000
Go back to your family.

370
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:29,900
Nothing will fall through the cracks.
We'll keep you informed.

371
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:32,400
That's a promise.

372
00:40:36,100 --> 00:40:37,700

So here we are.

373
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:40,800
Just two more drug smugglers.

374
00:40:41,500 --> 00:40:44,800
I don 't even know why
I'm making this tape.

375
00:41:07,100 --> 00:41:08,700
How do you do?

376
00:41:09,200 --> 00:41:10,700
I'm Henry Greene.

377
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:13,400
Hank Greene, actually.

378
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:15,600
- Who are you?
- Yankee Hank?

379
00:41:15,900 --> 00:41:20,500
Yankee Hank, or Hank the Yank,
or whatever.

380
00:41:20,900 --> 00:41:25,200
What can I do for you?
You want a cigarette?

381
00:41:25,600 --> 00:41:29,700
- So you're like a lawyer?
- No, I am a lawyer.

382
00:41:31,300 --> 00:41:34,100
Is this pro bono work that you do?

383
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:37,300
Pro bono? No.

384
00:41:37,900 --> 00:41:40,900
So I listened to your narrative.

385
00:41:43,100 --> 00:41:46,900
Forgive me if I'm blunt,
but there's nothing there.

386
00:41:47,300 --> 00:41:52,000
You just claim you didn't know
about the smack. If you're lying...

387
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:56,700
...you're brainy and stupid.
If it's true, you're just stupid.

388
00:41:57,100 --> 00:41:59,800
So I gotta ask a few questions.

389
00:42:00,300 --> 00:42:04,300
Who was carrying
the luggage with the drugs?

390
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:06,200
I was.

391
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:12,100
You had a couple kilos of heroin.
You didn't notice the extra weight?

392
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:15,900
- I didn't. I just didn't.
- We were late.

393
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:17,600
Yeah, of course.

394
00:42:18,100 --> 00:42:20,800
- Who packed the bag?
- I did.

395
00:42:24,700 --> 00:42:27,500
Alice, what does your father do?

396
00:42:27,800 --> 00:42:29,400
Works at Bekins.

397
00:42:29,700 --> 00:42:33,400
- Does he run a branch office?
- He rents trucks.

398
00:42:34,500 --> 00:42:36,200
And your mom?

399
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:39,300
She died when I was 7.

400
00:42:39,600 --> 00:42:42,100
Sorry to hear that.
What happened?

401
00:42:42,500 --> 00:42:44,200
Car accident.

402
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:47,900
- And your dad?
- Insurance.

403
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:51,900
And my mom sells real estate.
Part-time.

404
00:42:54,100 --> 00:42:57,000
I'll call to see
if they'll contribute...

405
00:42:57,300 --> 00:42:59,900
...to their daughters' liberation
fund.

406
00:43:00,300 --> 00:43:03,100
- What are you gonna do?
- Get you out.

407
00:43:03,400 --> 00:43:06,700
Start writing letters
to lawmakers back home.

408
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:11,300
Congressmen. The president.
If you know a priest.

409
00:43:11,800 --> 00:43:14,500
You want me to write
to my congressman?

410
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:17,700
That's right. I'll be in touch, girls.

411
00:43:22,200 --> 00:43:24,900
- He's totally sleazy.
- Don't say that.

412
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:27,900
Greene? You say you're Thai?

413
00:43:28,300 --> 00:43:30,000

Well, I might as well be.

414
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:33,600
I'm American, but I know
their justice system.

415
00:43:34,200 --> 00:43:36,700
- Now there's an oxymoron.
- Yeah.

416
00:43:37,900 --> 00:43:41,900
My wife, Yon,
is also a practicing attorney...

417
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:43,700
...born in Bangkok.

418
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:48,800
We've helped a lot of families.
We could help your daughter.

419
00:43:49,400 --> 00:43:51,300
What do you want out of this?

420
00:43:51,900 --> 00:43:54,100
I'm just a broker.

421
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:58,300
We're looking for our usual retainer.

422
00:43:58,600 --> 00:44:00,900
Which is...

423
00:44:01,200 --> 00:44:02,700
...$ 15,000.

424
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:04,800
$ 15,000?

425
00:44:06,200 --> 00:44:10,400
7500 to try to get a hearing
and 7500 if we do.

426
00:44:10,800 --> 00:44:13,700
That's for both girls.

427
00:44:14,400 --> 00:44:16,300
Wait, for both girls?

428
00:44:16,800 --> 00:44:21,200
- Darlene needs her own trial.
- You don't want to do that.

429
00:44:21,600 --> 00:44:26,000
The strongest point is
that Alice didn't sign a confession.

430
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:31,900
Separate them, and you're begging
for Darlene to be singled out.

431
00:44:34,900 --> 00:44:37,900
Do you wanna take a day or two?

432
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:40,000
No. God, no.

433
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:42,800
I'll get the money.

434
00:44:43,100 --> 00:44:46,000
I'll call Marano
and wire it to you.

435
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:49,300
Great. We'll be in touch.

436
00:45:10,900 --> 00:45:13,000
Who got you these tickets?

437
00:45:13,300 --> 00:45:16,300
Same guy who introduced me
to these babies.

438
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,400
Well, hello there. Thank you.

439
00:45:21,100 --> 00:45:23,200
Our next Minister of Justice.

440
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:25,500
He's worked hard for it.

441
00:45:25,800 --> 00:45:28,400
He's working his fingers to the bone.

442
00:45:32,100 --> 00:45:35,300
I love that guy!
I love that guy, man!

443
00:45:35,600 --> 00:45:36,700
This is great.

444
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:39,000
No problem.

445
00:45:39,300 --> 00:45:42,700
So when do I get the file
on Davis and Marano?

446
00:45:44,700 --> 00:45:48,500
Those girls have no chance
of getting out of there.

447
00:45:48,800 --> 00:45:50,300
Who's Nick Parks?

448
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:51,900
Who?

449
00:45:52,600 --> 00:45:55,000
Why couldn't you find him?

450
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:59,200
The cops say the girls made him up.

451
00:45:59,500 --> 00:46:02,100
Even if he did plant the six kilos...

452
00:46:02,400 --> 00:46:05,100
...you know he'd never confess.

453
00:46:05,600 --> 00:46:06,700
- Six?
- Yeah.

454
00:46:07,100 --> 00:46:09,400
The shit was in their backpacks.

455
00:46:10,200 --> 00:46:15,100
As far as the Thais are concerned,
they're guilty. Guilty or not.

456
00:46:15,500 --> 00:46:17,500
Take a pass on this one.

457
00:46:19,400 --> 00:46:21,900
After you give me the file, Roy.

458
00:46:29,700 --> 00:46:33,000
Why not find out
who bought the plane tickets?

459
00:46:33,600 --> 00:46:37,900
You'd think that'd be the easiest way
to catch this guy.

460
00:46:38,300 --> 00:46:40,300
If he exists.

461
00:46:41,500 --> 00:46:43,500
He sure doesn't exist in this.

462
00:46:43,900 --> 00:46:45,700
What do you believe?

463
00:46:46,900 --> 00:46:49,200
I believe that, either way...

464
00:46:49,500 --> 00:46:52,600
...we'll be able to afford a new car.

465
00:46:53,000 --> 00:46:55,200
This is Jagkrit's trophy photo.

466
00:46:56,000 --> 00:47:00,500
Look at that, they're so arrogant,
they don't try to finesse it.

467
00:47:00,900 --> 00:47:04,100
All that narcotic
in that little backpack.

468
00:47:05,500 --> 00:47:07,000
I don't think so.

469
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:17,400
- That's great.
- It's just a hearing for a retrial.

470
00:47:17,800 --> 00:47:21,400
I also talked to
the lady who runs the hotel.

471
00:47:21,800 --> 00:47:26,100
Either she's not involved
or she's the best liar I've met.

472
00:47:26,500 --> 00:47:28,300
What about Nick?

473
00:47:29,300 --> 00:47:31,400
Parks isn't the magic bullet.

474
00:47:31,700 --> 00:47:35,400
Even if we do find him,
it's your word against his.

475
00:47:36,100 --> 00:47:38,100
But we're still looking.

476
00:47:39,900 --> 00:47:42,800
Darlene, I need a moment with Alice.

477
00:47:43,900 --> 00:47:45,300
Sure.

478
00:47:55,000 --> 00:47:58,100
Nick was staying at
the Queen Victoria?

479
00:47:59,500 --> 00:48:02,200
My wife found a maid there...

480
00:48:02,500 --> 00:48:07,400
...who said there was a young man
there who matched Parks' description.

481
00:48:08,300 --> 00:48:09,600
So, good, right?

482
00:48:11,200 --> 00:48:13,700
The maid remembered him with a girl.

483
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:15,900
But when showed this picture...

484
00:48:16,200 --> 00:48:20,500
...guess who the maid picked out
as the girl he was with.

485
00:48:22,900 --> 00:48:23,700
Me.

486
00:48:25,600 --> 00:48:28,200
Okay, I was at Nick's hotel.

487
00:48:28,500 --> 00:48:32,400
And he came on to me,
but I told him to forget it.

488
00:48:33,500 --> 00:48:36,900
He never even mentioned drugs.
I swear it.

489
00:48:37,800 --> 00:48:41,200
- Is there anything else I should know?
- No.

490
00:48:43,900 --> 00:48:48,300
Do you have to tell Darlene?
That would be really weird.

491
00:48:50,100 --> 00:48:53,200
- I see no reason to tell anyone.
- Thank you.

492
00:48:54,600 --> 00:48:57,100
Now I have a favor to ask you.

493
00:48:57,400 --> 00:48:59,800
I haven't gotten your father's check.

494
00:49:01,500 --> 00:49:04,800
I need you to talk to him.

495
00:49:18,100 --> 00:49:20,500
Hi, hello. Hi.

496
00:49:23,600 --> 00:49:24,800
Alice?

497
00:49:26,300 --> 00:49:27,700
My God...

498
00:49:28,100 --> 00:49:29,500
Are you okay?

499
00:49:30,800 --> 00:49:32,700
Where are you? You sound close.

500
00:49:34,000 --> 00:49:36,400
I'm still here in Thailand.

501
00:49:38,700 --> 00:49:42,600
I'm trying to get there.
I would have been there sooner...

502
00:49:43,400 --> 00:49:47,600
It ain't about money,
but the doc says my diabetes...

503
00:49:49,100 --> 00:49:51,500
I don't have much time.

504
00:49:51,900 --> 00:49:54,700
I'm here with that lawyer,
Hank Greene.

505
00:49:57,000 --> 00:49:59,500
He needs his money
for the hearing.

506
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:04,400
I know, I talked to Doug about it.

507
00:50:04,800 --> 00:50:06,700
And I got your money.

508
00:50:10,300 --> 00:50:12,100
Daddy.

509
00:50:14,000 --> 00:50:16,200
