has earned you a few shekels?

759
01:22:15,300 --> 01:22:17,000
A few.

760
01:22:17,500 --> 01:22:21,500
I believe I'm really the source
of your good fortune.

761
01:22:22,800 --> 01:22:24,300
How's that, sir?

762
01:22:24,600 --> 01:22:28,000
I catch drug smugglers,
and you defend them.

763
01:22:28,300 --> 01:22:32,100
I feel I'm owed some sort of
tribute from you.

764
01:22:32,700 --> 01:22:35,300
It's a regular food chain.

765
01:22:35,600 --> 01:22:38,600
Yes, that's exactly what it is.

766
01:22:39,000 --> 01:22:43,000
I guess Skip Carn would know
a thing or two...

767
01:22:43,400 --> 01:22:45,900
...about paying tribute to you.

768
01:22:48,100 --> 01:22:50,700
I expect a little more from you.

769
01:22:50,900 --> 01:22:55,400
You're acting like...
What's that American expression?

770
01:22:55,800 --> 01:22:57,900
An ambulance chaser.

771
01:22:58,600 --> 01:23:03,600
I'm kind of a loose cannon.
Know that American expression?

772
01:23:04,000 --> 01:23:07,200
I'd love to blow this
out of the water.

773
01:23:07,500 --> 01:23:12,300
You have a cozy relationship
with a known drug trafficker.

774
01:23:12,800 --> 01:23:15,900
This is exactly the kind of thing...

775
01:23:16,200 --> 01:23:19,000
...Americans love watching on TV.

776
01:23:19,400 --> 01:23:24,200
Two American girls' lives ruined
by a sleazy smuggler...

777
01:23:24,600 --> 01:23:27,600
...and the greedy cop in his pocket.

778
01:23:28,100 --> 01:23:33,000
You'll have to get ready for
Larry King. You'll love him.

779
01:23:33,400 --> 01:23:37,600
Barbara Walters will probably
have pictures of you.

780
01:23:38,000 --> 01:23:42,200
Barbara and the parents
will go into the bedroom:

781
01:23:42,600 --> 01:23:47,100
"This is Darlene's room,
exactly as she left it."

782
01:23:47,500 --> 01:23:51,200
- Teddy bears...
- Is there a point to this fantasy?

783
01:23:51,600 --> 01:23:55,200
Yes, sir, it's a simple point.

784
01:23:55,900 --> 01:23:57,700
I need your help.

785
01:24:07,900 --> 01:24:09,900
That's a good accent.

786
01:24:10,200 --> 01:24:14,300
My Spanish teacher always told me,
"Good ear, bad memory."

787
01:24:15,700 --> 01:24:19,500
- How's Darlene doing?
- She's better.

788
01:24:21,300 --> 01:24:25,700
- We'll just wait for her.
- Can I ask you something?

789
01:24:26,200 --> 01:24:29,600
Since there's no money left,
why are you here?

790
01:24:30,600 --> 01:24:34,600
No matter how I look at it,
you don't deserve this.

791
01:24:36,700 --> 01:24:40,800
- Even if I did it?
- Yeah, but...

792
01:24:41,800 --> 01:24:45,200
You didn't do it.
We both know it.

793
01:24:58,900 --> 01:25:02,100
I wanted you to hear this
at the same time.

794
01:25:03,100 --> 01:25:05,100
You're gonna get to go home.

795
01:25:07,500 --> 01:25:11,400
- How?
- You'll have to sign a statement.

796
01:25:11,700 --> 01:25:14,400
Admit you're wrong. Forget Nick...

797
01:25:14,900 --> 01:25:17,700
- A statement?
- I can't do that.

798
01:25:18,000 --> 01:25:21,900
This is the official,
face-saving confession.

799
01:25:22,300 --> 01:25:26,100
You corroborate the police
version of events.

800
01:25:26,500 --> 01:25:28,900
That's our part of the deal.

801
01:25:30,200 --> 01:25:33,400
Then the crown will pardon you.

802
01:25:33,800 --> 01:25:35,600
Then you get to go home.

803
01:26:26,300 --> 01:26:27,700
All right.

804
01:26:28,900 --> 01:26:30,400
It's okay.

805
01:27:34,700 --> 01:27:37,500
No pardon: Narcotic offender.

806
01:27:38,000 --> 01:27:41,000
- What's the problem?
- No pardon.

807
01:27:41,300 --> 01:27:44,600
Your Minister of Justice has agreed.

808
01:27:44,900 --> 01:27:48,300
You tell him that we have
an agreement.

809
01:27:48,700 --> 01:27:53,300
I'm sorry.
They are narcotics smugglers.

810
01:27:53,700 --> 01:27:56,600
You son of a bitch, we have a deal.

811
01:27:56,900 --> 01:28:00,700
Yes, nicely done.
You really had me going.

812
01:28:01,100 --> 01:28:04,300
But now there is no more Skip Carn.

813
01:28:04,700 --> 01:28:07,600
No one will get to him, so no deal.

814
01:28:12,700 --> 01:28:13,900
Wait.

815
01:28:18,000 --> 01:28:19,900
No, get them off me.

816
01:28:48,700 --> 01:28:50,800
You may speak English.

817
01:28:52,300 --> 01:28:56,800
My best friend is not a drug smuggler.
She is innocent.

818
01:28:57,600 --> 01:28:59,100
She's innocent.

819
01:28:59,400 --> 01:29:02,400
All she ever did wrong
was to trust me.

820
01:29:05,000 --> 01:29:09,500
Here you believe one friend
knows what the other does.

821
01:29:09,900 --> 01:29:11,600
Maybe that's friendship...

822
01:29:11,900 --> 01:29:16,200
...but I'm American, and I was not
that kind of a friend.

823
01:29:16,600 --> 01:29:18,500
I know this.

824
01:29:20,800 --> 01:29:24,200
Because I did it.
Because I was foolish...

825
01:29:25,900 --> 01:29:29,900
...and jealous.
I was afraid she'd drift away.

826
01:29:30,300 --> 01:29:33,300
I was afraid I was gonna lose her.

827
01:29:34,900 --> 01:29:37,400
She never knew. It was all me.

828
01:29:37,700 --> 01:29:42,000
She spent all this time
in your prison for my mistakes.

829
01:29:43,400 --> 01:29:45,200
I'm sorry.

830
01:29:46,500 --> 01:29:50,700
Please, if you need someone
to do the time, I'll do it.

831
01:29:51,100 --> 01:29:55,300
I'll do her time and mine.
Just let her go, please.

832
01:30:07,100 --> 01:30:12,000
Then you're of strong character
and would lie to save your friend?

833
01:30:13,200 --> 01:30:16,000
No, I am of weak character.

834
01:30:16,500 --> 01:30:19,800
And I just want to
make up for my mistakes.

835
01:30:20,200 --> 01:30:23,300
If you're lying to
save your friend...

836
01:30:24,000 --> 01:30:28,100
...then you're of sufficient character
to earn what you want.

837
01:30:29,300 --> 01:30:31,700
If you're telling the truth...

838
01:30:32,000 --> 01:30:36,300
...then your friend is innocent
and should go free.

839
01:30:36,700 --> 01:30:40,800
If you are willing to serve
her term and yours...

840
01:30:41,300 --> 01:30:43,600
...your friend is pardoned.

841
01:30:49,500 --> 01:30:51,900
Thank you. Thank you.

842
01:31:26,800 --> 01:31:29,300
Darlene must go soon.

843
01:31:47,100 --> 01:31:49,300
You're a very good liar.

844
01:31:50,500 --> 01:31:52,300
You didn't do it.

845
01:31:53,700 --> 01:31:55,800
I know you didn't do it.

846
01:31:57,100 --> 01:31:59,100
I don't think I can leave you.

847
01:32:02,700 --> 01:32:05,100
If I say it was the truth...

848
01:32:05,700 --> 01:32:09,200
...you'll hate me.
And if I say I lied...

849
01:32:09,500 --> 01:32:14,600
...then when you go home,
all the time with your family...

850
01:32:15,000 --> 01:32:17,800
You won't be able to just be happy.

851
01:32:19,600 --> 01:32:23,400
So let's just say it was
the right thing to do.

852
01:32:28,500 --> 01:32:30,800
Let's just leave it at that.

853
01:32:42,000 --> 01:32:43,200
Come, Darlene.

854
01:32:54,500 --> 01:32:57,900
- I'm going to get you out of here.
- I know.

855
01:33:01,800 --> 01:33:05,600
Go, Dar. I need you to.

856
01:33:07,200 --> 01:33:08,800
Please.

857
01:34:44,100 --> 01:34:48,600
 A lot of people won 't
understand why I said I did it.

858
01:34:49,000 --> 01:34:52,000
But for me, it was
the right thing to do.

859
01:34:52,900 --> 01:34:56,300
Maybe more right than
anything I ever did.

860
01:34:57,900 --> 01:35:01,100
Darlene and Hank won 't stop trying...

861
01:35:02,200 --> 01:35:04,100
...till I'm out of here.

862
01:35:05,400 --> 01:35:07,000
Until I'm free.

